 of both high society and popular culture at the time. Courting Celebrity illustrates women’s practice in two key literary genres, poetry and autobiography, and illuminates the strategies of women’s self-fashioning and pursuit of celebrity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAutobiographieszItaly. 0aWomen poets, Italiany19th centuryvBiography. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Italian.2bisacsh  aAglaja Anassillide.  aAngela Veronese.  aItalian literature.  aTeresa Bandettini.  aVenice and Venetian culture.  aautobiography.  acelebrity.  agardens.  apastoral poetry.  apoet-improviser.  asalons.  asociability.  awomen’s writing.1 aWard, Adrienne , econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWard, Adrienne , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZanini-Cordi, Irene , econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZanini-Cordi, Irene , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z978311131826408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079736740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148754642740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487546427423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487546427/original  a978-3-11-079736-7  University of Toronto Pr